;B[ss]LB[ms:1][ss:2][ps:A]C[Dia. 02 Opponent's Vital Point

{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}

White can't capture Black if he simply takes at 1, because Black can play the vital point at 2.

The proverb which says "\cf1\b The opponent's vital point is my vital point\cf0\b0 " works very well.

Actually if Black blocks at A instead of 2, it is also good.


])
