{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}

However if there is a White stone at \'a1\'e2, it is not good to block at 1.

If Black plays like that, White's attachment at 2 is severe. It is also the \cf1\b 1-2 vital point\cf0\b0 .

Black has to start the pae with 3. It is always important to pay attention of the outside liberties.
